          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for private or public recitation and prayer in praise of the river Sarasvatī personified by the Hindu goddess of the same name. Manuscript has two parts, the first, in ten verses, is a short Vedic hymn (sūkta) to Sarasvatī and the second is a praise text (stotra) to the same goddess.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Sarasvatīstotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">सरस्वतीस्तोत्र+</title>
              <author>
